to the editor i appreciated james reston jr 's perspective on organ transplant donation op ed aug 7 from the other side of the experience at 34 i became a widow in one swift day the decision to donate my husband 's organs was not easy in the nightmare of the moment i clung to the hope of his recovery ultimately a different kind of hope came to me that of giving the gift of life to others i agree that families not just politicians should be involved in policy decisions about transplants and organ donation who can speak better to the concerns and issues of this miraculous and grievously complex experience rose d'acquisto st paul aug 7 2002 the writer is a member of the national donor family council of the national kidney foundation in new york

